<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,781,1022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">
<taxonomicName box="[151,444,781,805]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="obsoleta" subSpecies="pleuralis">
<emphasis box="[151,444,781,805]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">Centris obsoleta pleuralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[451,553,781,806]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">lectotype</typeStatus>
(♀, 
<figureCitation box="[606,737,781,806]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 20" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1077,1933]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,1077,1933]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 20. Lectotype (♀) Centris obsoleta pleuralis Friese, 1901 (= Centris (Melacentris) obsoleta Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau, 1841): Fig. 17. Head, frontal view; Fig. 18. Habitus, lateral view; Fig. 19. Habitus, dorsal view; Fig. 20. Wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/227852/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">
Figs 
<number box="[662,737,782,806]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17–20</number>
</figureCitation>
): Friese based the description on a manuscript name provided by Mocsáry (“Mocs. i. l.” or Mocsáry 
<emphasis box="[595,699,817,841]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">in litteris</emphasis>
) from an unknown number of specimens in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" box="[1214,1304,818,841]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">HNHM</collectionCode>
. The single female labeled “Piauchy / 
<collectingCountry box="[455,542,853,878]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">Brasilia</collectingCountry>
[printed]”, “ 
<number box="[688,732,854,878]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" value="848.0">848</number>
/ 
<number box="[758,789,854,878]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" value="87.0">87</number>
”, “ 
<number box="[826,858,854,878]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" value="28.0">28</number>
.” [green label], “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1055,1185,853,877]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis box="[1055,1074,854,877]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1090,1185,853,877]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
♀ / v. 
<taxonomicName box="[1269,1369,853,877]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pleuralis">
<emphasis box="[1269,1369,853,877]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">pleuralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ det. 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese" box="[151,285,889,914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Trigona - Arten Australiens. Termeszetrajzi Fuzetek, 21, 427 - 431." type="journal article" year="1898">
Friese 
<number box="[229,285,890,914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" value="1898.0">1898</number>
</bibRefCitation>
/ Mocs.” is here designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[692,799,889,914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[864,912,890,914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">type</typeStatus>
locality is Piauí, 
<collectingCountry box="[1117,1188,889,914]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and according to the accession book at 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" box="[357,442,926,949]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">HNHM</collectionCode>
the specimen was purchased from E. Menkl in 
<number box="[982,1041,926,950]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" value="1889.0">1889</number>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[1053,1274,925,950]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical region, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba (Parana), pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[1135,1185,925,949]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1207,1266,926,950]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,926,949]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,246,961,985]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[309,447,961,985]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pleuralis">
<emphasis box="[309,328,962,985]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[347,447,961,985]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">pleuralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as two valid and distinct species. However, our examination of both primary 
<typeStatus box="[1377,1436,962,986]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">types</typeStatus>
indicates the opposite and they are here considered synonymies. A 
<typeStatus box="[903,990,998,1022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1027,1155,997,1021]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obsoleta">
<emphasis box="[1027,1046,998,1021]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1060,1155,997,1021]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">obsoleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in 
<collectionCode box="[1216,1326,998,1022]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">OUMNH</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
